      <dsc type="in-depth">
         <head>Item Listing</head>
         <c01 level="series" id="d1e193">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Letters</unittitle>
            </did>
            <c02 level="item" id="d1e197">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>
                     <persname>William Slade</persname>to 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot
                  Griswold</persname>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate>1838 July 28</unitdate>
                  <physdesc>
                     <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
                     <extent>2 p.</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>[Requests publication of excerpts from the 
                  <bibref>Emancipator</bibref>and his correspondence
                  with students of 
                  <corpname>Bangor Theological Seminary</corpname>which
                  had appeared in the 
                  <bibref>Evangelist</bibref>. ]</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="item" id="d1e228">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>
                     <persname>[John Lewis] O'Sullivan</persname>to 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot
                  Griswold</persname>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate>1841 July 5</unitdate>
                  <physdesc>
                     <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
                     <extent>1 p.</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>[Accompanying the corrected copy of a report.
                  Offers to write a preface to it. Sends respects to
                  Mr. 
                  <persname>[Richard Henry] Dana</persname>and inquires
                  about the cost of 10,000 copies of the report.]</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="item" id="d1e253">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>
                     <persname>Thomas Colley Grattan</persname>to 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot
                  Griswold</persname>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate>1843 January 16</unitdate>
                  <physdesc>
                     <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
                     <extent>2 p.</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>[Comments on a melancholy letter received from 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot Griswold</persname>and
                  negotiates the sale of two tales to 
                  <bibref>Graham's Magazine</bibref>. ]</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="item" id="d1e281">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>
                     <persname>Thomas Colley Grattan</persname>to 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot
                  Griswold</persname>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate>1843 November 27</unitdate>
                  <physdesc>
                     <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
                     <extent>3 p.</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>[Acknowledges receipt of three copies of his short
                  story and expresses concern over its having been
                  published in an unauthorized form. Also asks about
                  the payment he will receive for it.]</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="item" id="d1e303">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>
                     <persname>Hiram Ketcham</persname>to 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot
                  Griswold</persname>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate>1844 April 1</unitdate>
                  <physdesc>
                     <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
                     <extent>1 p.</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>[Regrets he cannot comply with the request for an
                  article on Romanism because of other
                  commitments.]</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="item" id="d1e325">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>
                     <persname>Thomas Bangs Thorpe</persname>to 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot
                  Griswold</persname>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate>1845 May 15</unitdate>
                  <physdesc>
                     <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
                     <extent>1 p.</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>[Accompanying a biographical sketch. Expresses
                  appreciation for Griswold's contributions to American
                  literature. Suggests that the first great original
                  national writing will come from the south.]</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="item" id="d1e347">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>[ 
                  <persname>Thomas Dow Jones</persname>] to 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot
                  Griswold</persname>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate>[1846] February 24</unitdate>
                  <physdesc>
                     <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
                     <extent>1 p.</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>[Requests that Griswold call briefly to see his
                  sculpture.]</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="item" id="d1e369">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>
                     <persname>L. R. [Koecker]</persname>to 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot
                  Griswold</persname>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate>1850 November 1</unitdate>
                  <physdesc>
                     <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
                     <extent>1p.</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>[Concerns his recent trip to 
                  <geogname>Europe</geogname>, the publication of the 
                  <bibref>Life of Poe</bibref>and the 
                  <bibref>Life of Paul Jones</bibref>. Requests letters
                  of 
                  <persname>Washington Irving</persname>, 
                  <persname>George Payne Rainsford</persname>, or other
                  "worthies."]</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="item" id="d1e406">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>
                     <persname>Lewis Cass</persname>to 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot Griswold</persname>(Body of
                  letter in hand of clerk)</unittitle>
                  <unitdate>1851 December 15</unitdate>
                  <physdesc>
                     <genreform>LS,</genreform>
                     <extent>2 p.</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>[Regrets his inability to participate in planning
                  a memorial to 
                  <persname>James Fenimore Cooper</persname>and
                  expresses his admiration of Cooper's work.]</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="item" id="d1e432">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>
                     <persname>H. F. Phinney</persname>to 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot
                  Griswold</persname>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate>1852 July 17</unitdate>
                  <physdesc>
                     <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
                     <extent>2 p.</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>[Announces gift of Cooper's 
                  <bibref>History of the Navy</bibref>to 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot Griswold</persname>and
                  requests any letters regarding Mr. Cooper addressed
                  to Mr. 
                  <persname>[Washington] Irving</persname>or 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot Griswold</persname>be sent to
                  him.]</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="item" id="d1e467">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>
                     <persname>Charles Augustus Stetson</persname>to 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot
                  Griswold</persname>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate>1853 January 13</unitdate>
                  <physdesc>
                     <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
                     <extent>2 p.</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>[Asks that he call to discuss with Mr. 
                  <persname>[Horatio] Greenough</persname>the
                  intentions of the Bostonians regarding publication of
                  " 
                  <bibref>The Memorial</bibref>. "]</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="item" id="d1e495">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>
                     <persname>Henry Charles Carey</persname>to 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot
                  Griswold</persname>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate>1853 May 14</unitdate>
                  <physdesc>
                     <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
                     <extent>2 p.</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>[Concerns an accident in which 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot Griswold</persname>'s daughter
                  was injured. Mentions his book which he hoped 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot Griswold</persname>would "give
                  notice of."]</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="item" id="d1e523">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>
                     <persname>Henry Charles Carey</persname>to 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot
                  Griswold</persname>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate>1853 September 29</unitdate>
                  <physdesc>
                     <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
                     <extent>2 p.</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>[Indicates his desire to visit 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot Griswold</persname>while in 
                  <geogname>New York</geogname>. ]</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="item" id="d1e551">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>
                     <persname>John Jay Smith</persname>to 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot
                  Griswold</persname>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate>1854 December 11</unitdate>
                  <physdesc>
                     <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
                     <extent>1 p.</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>[Expresses appreciation of 
                  <bibref>The Republican Court</bibref>in which several
                  ancestors ( 
                  <persname>James Logan</persname>, a Morris, a Neill, 
                  <persname>Thomas Lloyd</persname>, the 
                  <famname>Moore</famname>s) are mentioned. Indicates a
                  volume on the 
                  <famname>Neill family</famname>is being sent to 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot Griswold</persname>]</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
            <c02 level="item" id="d1e592">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>
                     <persname>[John Lewis] O'Sullivan</persname>to 
                  <persname>Rufus Wilmot
                  Griswold</persname>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate>n.d.</unitdate>
                  <physdesc>
                     <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
                     <extent>3 p.</extent>
                  </physdesc>
               </did>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>[Inquires about a story submitted for publication,
                  and rates paid various authors such as 
                  <persname>[Nathaniel Parker] Willis</persname>and 
                  <persname>[Caroline Matilda] Kirkland</persname>.
                  Also asks when 
                  <bibref>Rev. Ballads and Anecdotes of the American
                  Bar</bibref>will be sent.]</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c02>
         </c01>
      </dsc>
